<http://drug.uk/hyoscine-butylbromide> <http://drug.uk/model/sideEffectDescription> "Common or very common\nConstipation; dizziness; drowsiness; dry mouth; dyspepsia; flushing; headache; nausea; palpitations; skin reactions; tachycardia; urinary disorders; vision disorders; vomiting\nRare or very rare\nAngioedema; confusion (more common in elderly)\n General side-effects:\nFrequency not known\nDyspnoea\nSpecific side-effects:\nFrequency not known\nWith parenteral use\nAnaphylactic reaction; feeling hot; hypotension; mydriasis; sweat changes" .
